{{wiktionary|hush money}} '''Hush money''' is an informal term for [[bribery|financial incentives or rewards (bribery)]] offered in exchange for not divulging information.
'''Hush Money''' may also refer to: * [[Hush Money (1921 film)|''Hush Money'' (1921 film)]], a 1921 silent film directed by [[Charles Maigne]] * ''[[Hush Money]]'', a 1931 comedy film directed by Sidney Lanfield and featuring Joan Bennett, Myrna Loy, and George Raft * [[Hush Money (novel)|''Hush Money'' (novel)]], a 1999 mystery novel by [[Robert B. Parker]]
